  "function_path": "pkg/kubelet/eviction/eviction_manager.go",
  "function_name": "synchronize",
  "justification": "This is a method on managerImpl that performs a single synchronization cycle of the node eviction manager. It evaluates current resource usage against configured thresholds and selects/terminates workloads if necessary. The function takes context, disk info provider, and active pods function as parameters. It returns evicted pods and error. The procedure matches exactly: it refreshes memory threshold notifiers from summary stats (lines 301-308), computes signal observations (line 311), determines which thresholds are met (lines 315-346), tracks observation timestamps, filters thresholds by grace periods and stats updates (line 356), checks local storage violations first (lines 364-368), performs node-level reclamation (lines 387-389), ranks pods using signal-specific functions (lines 394-410), and evicts the first killable pod (lines 421-443). It updates internal state including met thresholds, node condition timestamps, and observation history (lines 349-360)."
}

